HEADWORD: Athermanous
<hw>A*ther"ma*nous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <grk>qermai`nein</grk> to heat, <grk>qe`rma</grk>
heat: cf. F. <ets>athermane</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Not
transmitting heat; -- opposed to <contr>diathermanous</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Athermous</ent>⟦br⟧
